itemDescription: British educationalist, headmaster at Oundle School from 1922 to 1945

wikipedia_page.main: Kenneth Fisher JP (18 July 1882 – 2 October 1945) was a British educator and ornithologist. He was headmaster of Oundle School, an independent school in Oundle, Northamptonshire, England, run by the Worshipful Company of Grocers, from 1922 to 1945

response: * Kenneth Fisher (headmaster) (1882–1945), headmaster of Oundle School
